“What the hell,” panted Ron, holding up the Horcrux, which swung backward and forward on its shortened chain in some parody of hypnosis, “didn’t
you take this thing off before you dived?”
Harry could not answer. The silver doe was nothing, nothing compared with
Ron’s reappearance: he could not believe it. Shuddering with cold, he caught
up the pile of clothes still lying at the water’s edge and began to pull them on.
