As Scabior said it, Harry’s scar, which was stretched tight across his distended forehead, burned savagely. More clearly than he could make out anything around him, he saw a towering building, a grim fortress, jet-black and
forbidding: Voldemort’s thoughts had suddenly become Razor-Sharp again; he
was gliding toward the gigantic building with a sense of calmly euphoric purpose . . . .
So close . . . So close . . .
